    {
      "id": "3364750c-f3ba-8071-92c0-f4d0c025bb7a",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "KT techniques, while good at achieving good accuracies on different benchmark datasets, have often not focused on the impact of difficulty in knowledge modeling. Authors propose a Difficulty-Aware Programming Knowledge Tracing via Large Language Models (DPKT) that aims to improve at this component that is so important for open-ended questions such as programming challenges. \n\nResults show that Model performs excellently across different Language Datasets. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "3364750c-f3ba-8071-92c0-f4d0c025bb7a",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
